The life-expectancy gap between Indigenous and non-Indigenous Australians 
remains one of contemporary Australia's most enduring health divides. The 
reduction of observed health outcome disparity between population groups based 
on measures of socioeconomic status, geography, or ethnicity stands as a key 
target of coordinated societal and health system reform. CVD remains the 
principal cause of death among all Australian population groups, including 
